IFP councillor Mthembeni Majola has been shot dead in Estcourt, KwaZulu-Natal. JOHANNESBURG - IFP councillor Mthembeni Majola has been shot dead in Estcourt, KwaZulu-Natal. The alleged hit took place on Friday evening while he was driving. Unknown suspects opened fire on his vehicle. “Cllr Majola was killed in a hail of bullets in Estcourt last night at approximately 20H30, when two unknown vehicles over took Cllr Majola's vehcile and opened fire at a set of speed bumps,” IFP said in a statement. READ: IFP councillor killed in apparent ambush: report Police have confirmed Majola sustained multiple gunshot wounds and was declared dead on the scene. Two passengers in his car were rushed to hospital. READ: Another ANCYL leader gunned down in KZN Majola was a co-accused in a plot to murder the Endumeni municipal speaker. Police are investigating charges of murder and attempted murder in connection with Friday's shooting.